He emphasised the importance of investment in digital infrastructure in the region, saying "we don't want the digital divide to translate to an AI divide for Africa."

headline: Beijing drops Google probe, shifting focus to Nvidia in US trade talks, FT reports
summary: The move signals a tactical shift by Beijing, redirecting regulatory focus to Nvidia as leverage in the U.S.-China trade talks and sending a message of flexibility to Washington by ending the probe into Google, the newspaper said.  China's State Administration for Market Regulation, which opened the investigation against Google in February, has now decided to drop it, the report said citing two people briefed on the decision.
